BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BKswnT8DHgysnl59AGuIN
SUMMARY:Heron Habitat Helpers - Help us restore Kiwanis Ravine!
DTSTAMP:20260327T031553Z
DTSTART:20260411T090000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Kiwanis Memorial Preser
	ve Park. \\nWe’ll be grubbing out blackberry root crowns and spreading mul
	ch to prevent regrowth. The main blackberry stalks will already be cut\\\,
	 so we’ll focus on keeping the site healthy for native plants to thrive. \
	\nDesignated as Seattle Parks’ first official Wildlife Sanctuary in 2010\\
	\, Kiwanis Ravine is adjacent to Seattle’s largest Great Blue Heron colony
	—just a short walk from our work site! If you’re interested\\\, we’d love 
	to lead a short tour after the event. \\nVolunteers are welcome to join fo
	r any length of time. We’ll provide tools\\\, gloves\\\, and light snacks—
	just bring a full water bottle and wear clothes that can get muddy or snag
	ged. No experience necessary\\\, just enthusiasm for helping wildlife habi
	tat thrive! \\nRegister\n\nhttps://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/he
	ron-habitat-helpers-help-us-restore-kiwanis-ravine/\n\nFrom The Seattle Pa
	rks Foundation
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/heron-habitat-helpers-help
	-us-restore-kiwanis-ravine/
LOCATION:WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-parks-foundation
CATEGORIES:The Seattle Parks Foundation
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
